modules.description: This module handles parsing, formatting, and manipulation of dates and times according to the ISO 8601 standard. It provides core data types such as `date`, `time`, and `datetime`, along with operations to convert between them, adjust time zones, and perform comparisons. You can use it to parse a date string like `"2023-10-05"`, add durations to timestamps, or format a time value into a human-readable string. Specific examples include calculating the difference between two datetimes, normalizing time representations, and validating input strings against ISO 8601 formats.
